s can be taken to reduce worst effects. As a diagnostic method, RTM offers a statistically valid way to identify vulnerable places. To learn more, visit http://www.riskterrainmodeling.com and begin using RTM with the many free tutorials and resources.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAutomobile drivingxSocial aspectszEurope, Western. 0aAutomobilesxSocial aspectszEurope, Western. 0aCrime analysisxStatistical methods. 0aCrime forecastingxGeographic information systems. 0aCrime prevention. 0aCrimexEnvironmental aspects. 0aSpatial analysis (Statistics). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh1 aKennedy, Leslie W., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016z978311066754708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016z978311065748740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520958807423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520958807.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065748-7  UCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-066754-7  UC Press eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles